# Project Overview

## Repo layout

- `frontend/` — Vite + React + TypeScript
- `backend/` — NestJS + SQLite
- Root `README.md` with run instructions

## Code quality

- Clear, maintainable code first: small focused files, descriptive names
- No business logic in UI components — keep logic in `api/`, `hooks/`, `utils/`, or backend services
- Separation of concerns: pages compose; they do not fetch, validate, or transform data inline

## Reusable components

If the same UI appears twice (loader, empty state, error banner, todo row, category select), extract to `components/` and reuse. Do not copy-paste.

## Comments

Use `//` only for non-obvious business logic or complex algorithms. Do not comment trivial code.

## Error UX contract

- Backend returns human-readable `message` strings in JSON error responses
- Frontend displays those messages (snackbar/alert) — never swallow errors silently

## Feature checklist (test-task.md)

- Create todos with text + category
- Mark tasks completed; completed tasks stay 5s with Undo snackbar
- Delete tasks with Undo snackbar
- Filter by category (or "All")
- Max 5 tasks per category (backend enforces, frontend shows error)
- Loading, error, and empty states on the todos list
